 <span data-ttu-id="a9aa2-104">Au contrôle un <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>, le <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> doit faire référence à la <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> de la <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> qui contrôle la table <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a9aa2-104">To control a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>, the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> must reference the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> that controls that <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a9aa2-105">Consultez [Comment : utiliser les déclencheurs d’événements pour contrôler un Storyboard après démarrage](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) pour obtenir un exemple.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a9aa2-105">See [How to: Use Event Triggers to Control a Storyboard After It Starts](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) for an example.</span></span>  
  
